#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:3
msgid "Configuration File"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:5
msgid "You can control various behaviors of the Http server by configuring various parameters through multiple interfaces of the DrogonAppFramework instance. However, using a configuration file is a better way for the following reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:7
msgid "Using a configuration file instead of source code can determine the behavior of the application at runtime rather than at compile time, which is undoubtedly a more convenient and flexible way;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:8
msgid "Using a configuration file can make the main file more concise;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:10
msgid "Based on these additional benefits, it is recommended that application developers use configuration files to configure various parameters of the application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:12
msgid "The configuration file can be loaded very simply by calling the loadConfigFile() interface before calling the run() interface. The parameter of the loadConfigFile() method is the file name of the configuration file, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:14
msgid "*main.cc*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:23
msgid "The above program loads the configuration file *config.json* and then runs the application. The specific listening port, log output, database configuration and so on can be configured by the configuration file. In fact, this program can basically be the entire code of the main file of the web application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:27
msgid "Configuration File Details"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:29
msgid "An example of a configuration file is at the top level of the source directory, config.example.json. If you use the drogon_ctl create project command to create a project, you can also find the file config.json with the same content in the project directory. So, you basically don't need to create a new configuration file but make some changes to this file to complete the configuration of the web application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:31
msgid "The file is in *JSON* format and supports comments. You can comment out the unneeded configuration items with the c++ comment symbols /\\*\\*/ and //."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:33
msgid "After commenting out a configuration option, the framework initializes it with default values. The default value for each option can be found in the comments in the configuration file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:37
msgid "SSL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:39
msgid "The ssl option is to configure SSL files of the https service as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:48
msgid "Where *cert* is the path of the certificate file and *key* is the path of the private key file. If a file contains both a certificate and a private key, the two paths can be made the same."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:50
msgid "The file is in PEM encoding format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:54
msgid "listeners"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:56
msgid "As the name implies, the *listeners* option is to configure listeners for the web application. It is a JSON array type. Each JSON object represents a listener. The specific configuration is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:75
#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:105
#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:141
#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:200
#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:220
msgid "Among them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:77
msgid "*address*: With the string type indicates the IP address to be listened to. If this option is not available, the default value \"0.0.0.0\" is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:78
msgid "*port*: port: An integer type option indicating the port to be listened to. It must be a valid port number. There is no default value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:79
msgid "*https*: Boolean type, indicating whether to use https, the default value is false, which means using http."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:80
msgid "*cert* and *key*: The string type, is valid when https is true, indicating the certificate and private key of https. The default value is an empty string, indicating the certificate and private key file configured by the global option ssl;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:84
msgid "db_clients"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:86
msgid "This option is used to configure the database client. It is a JSON array type. Each JSON object represents a separate database client. The specific configuration is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:107
msgid "*name*: string type, client name, the default value is \"default\", name is the application developer to get the database client's markup from the framework, if there are multiple clients, the name field must be different;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:108
msgid "*rdbms*：A string indicating the type of database server. Currently supports \"postgresql\" and \"mysql\", which is not case sensitive;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:109
msgid "*host*：String, database server address, *localhost* is the default value;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:110
msgid "*port*：An integer representing the port number of the database server;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:111
msgid "*dbname*：String, database name;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:112
msgid "*user*：String, user name;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:113
msgid "*passwd*：String, password;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:114
msgid "*is_fast*：bool，false by default, indicate if the client is a FastDbClient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:115
msgid "*connection_number*：A integer indicating the number of connections to the database server, at least 1, the default value is also 1, affecting the concurrent performance of data read and write; If the 'is_fast' is true, the number is the number of connections per event loop, otherwise it is the total number of all connections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:116
msgid "*filename*: The filename of sqlite3 database;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:120
msgid "threads_num"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:122
msgid "Suboption belonging to the app option, an integer, the default value is 1, indicating the number of IO threads, which has a clear impact on network concurrency. This number is not as big as possible. Users who understand the non-blocking I/O principle should know that this value should be the same as the number of processors that he expects network IO to occupy. If the value is set to 0, the number of IO threads will be the number of all hardware cores."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:128
msgid "The above example shows that network IO uses 16 threads and can run up to 16 CPU cores under high load conditions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:132
msgid "Session"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:134
msgid "Session-related options are also children of the app option, controlling whether session is used and the session timeout. Such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:143
msgid "*enable_session*：A Boolean value indicating whether to use a session. The default is false. If the client does not support cookies, set it to false because the framework will create a new session for each request without a session cookie, which will result in completely unnecessary resource and performance loss;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:144
msgid "*session_timeout*：An integer value indicating the timeout period of the session, in seconds. The default value is 0, indicating permanent validity. Only works if enable_session is true."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:148
msgid "document_root"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:150
msgid "The suboption of the *app* option, a string, indicates the document path corresponding to the Http root directory, and is the root path of the static file download. The default value is \"./\", which indicates the current path of the program running. such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:158
msgid "upload_path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:160
msgid "The child of the app option, a string, represents the default path for uploading files. The default value is \"uploads\". If the value is not starting with /, ./ or ../, and this value is not .or..`, then this path is the relative path of the previous document_root entry, otherwise it is an absolute path or a relative path to the current directory. Such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:168
msgid "file_types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:170
msgid "The suboption of the app option, an array of strings, with default values ​​as follows, indicates the static file download type supported by the framework. If the requested static file extension is outside of these types, the framework will return a 404 error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:191
msgid "Connection number control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:193
msgid "The children of the app option have two options, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:202
msgid "*max_connections*：Integer, the default value is 100000, which means the maximum number of simultaneous concurrent connections; when the number of connections maintained by the server reaches this number, the new TCP connection request will be rejected directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:203
msgid "*max_connections_per_ip*：Integer, the default value is 0, which means the maximum number of connections for a single client IP, and 0 means no limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:207
msgid "Log option"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:209
msgid "The child of the *app* item, a JSON object, controls the behavior of the log output as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:222
msgid "*log_path*：String, the default value is an empty string, indicating the path where the log file is stored. If it is an empty string, all logs are output to the standard output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:223
msgid "*logfile_base_name*：A string indicating the basename of the log file. The default value is an empty string which means the basename will be drogon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:224
msgid "*log_size_limit*：A integer, in bytes. The default value is 100000000 (100M). When the size of the log file reaches this value, the log file will be switched."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:225
msgid "*log_level*：A string, the default value is \"DEBUG\", which indicates the lowest level of log output. The optional values ​​are from low to high: \"TRACE\", \"DEBUG\", \"INFO\", \"WARN\", where the TRACE level is only valid when compiling in DEBUG mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:228
msgid "Note: Drogon's file log uses a non-blocking output structure that can achieve a log output of millions of lines per second and can be used with confidence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:232
msgid "Application control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:234
msgid "They are also children of the *app* option and have two options, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:241
#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:302
#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:330
msgid "Among them："
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:243
msgid "*run_as_daemon*：Boolean value, the default value is false. When it is true, the application will be a child process of the No.1 process in the form of a daemon running in the background of the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:244
msgid "*relaunch_on_error*：Boolean value, the default value is false. When it is true, the application will relaunches itself on error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:248
msgid "use_sendfile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:250
msgid "The suboption of app option, boolean, indicates whether the linux system call sendfile is used when sending the file. The default value is true. Using sendfile can improve the sending efficiency and reduce the memory usage of large files. as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Configuration-File-en.rstd:257
msgid "Note: Even if this option is true, the sendfile system call will not be used, because the use of sendfile for small files is not necessarily cost-effective, and the framework will decide whether to adopt it according to its own optimization strategy."
msgstr ""

